The project Employee Management is implemented as an example of DAO Design Pattern and Singleton Design Pattern
Classes: 
	Employee - Pojo class holding the attributes and setter, getters
	EmployeeClient - The client class fires the implemented methods.
	EmployeeDAO - The class with core implementation of functionality
	EmployeeServiceImpl -The class implementing the interface created and triggers the DAO methods
	IEmployeeService - Interface holding the method signatures
	InvalidEmployeeCode - Custom Exception 
	ConnectionFact - Class responsible to pull db connection from available pool